I routinely see 76% quoted as the chance for 1 loser using two
finesses. While I don't feel up to doing the calculations a quick rule
of thumb says there is one chance out of 2 for an opponent to hold a
diamond honor. Consequently the odds of holding both is 1/2 time 1/2
or 1/4 so you win unless your LHO has both which comes to 75% odds of
making. BTW playing for the drop of one honor under the A or crashing
both together is essentially the same and only marginally inferior
(0-4 break is generally the difference I think).
