stiff honor onside you only need clubs 4-1. So, for 2-2 breaks we have
2/3*.40*.68+1/6*.40*.96=24.92%, for 3-1 breaks we have
1/2*.50*.96+1/4*.50*.68=32.33%, for 4-0 we have 1/2*.10*.96=4.598%.  All
together 61.85%.  Of course this ignores any effect one suit
breaking/not breaking will have on the other suit or the possibility
that west is stiff honor, stiff in the minors or void, void in the
minors.  Alternatively you could just play 6N and not worry about all of
this. :)

