Tricky one.

Crossing to dummy doesn't always fail if clubs are 4-1.

If diamonds are KQ(xx) onside (around 24%), or RHO has a stiff honour
(12%), you are safe, because you don't have to cross to dummy the second
time.

So of the 76% raw chance of picking up diamonds with 2 finesses, 40% is at
risk of clubs 4-1 (28%).  And almost all of it is at risk if clubs are 5-0
(4%).  So subtract about 14% from your original 76% to get 62% from the 2
finesses line.

So I think the 2 finesses line is around 62%.  Ace and another works about
66% of the time.

Now add in the intangible - no singleton club lead.  So now you have to
look at the auction, and the actual opening lead - was it from a major suit
sequence?

Toss a coin time.

Cheers ... Bill
